text: General elections were held in Cambodia on 10 June 1962.Dieter Nohlen, Florian Grotz & Christof Hartmann (2001) Elections in Asia: A data handbook, Volume II, p63 Only candidates of the Sangkum party were allowed to contest the election, although more than one candidate could run in a constituency.
